{
  "stem": "24814.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't think that-- I don't think people did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a prisoner-of-war interrogation team right with our combat command headquarters.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was a refugee from Germany, an anti-Nazi German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he loved interrogating those Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had a whole team there, but I would just spontaneously pick up-- the prisoners were so happy to be taken alive, and they'd heard so much propaganda about the Jewish-American, Roosevelt, Bolshevik murderers who were going to torture them and so on.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they found we were nice guys, we gave them-- [LAUGHS] bandaged up their wounds, gave them a shot, maybe something to eat.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That they'd talk.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't shut them up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Who their regiment was, where they were coming from, which officer they didn't like, who was a big Nazi, who wasn't.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yadda, yadda.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they-- they found I was not going to hurt them, I was helping them, and I spoke German.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I couldn't keep them quiet.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] There was no trouble getting information out of the wounded German prisoners.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, exactly like ours.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I took care of hundreds and hundreds of wounded Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was after the breakthrough started, yeah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I left off with the Battle of the Bulge, our end of it, the Alsatian Bulge.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went-- then we went down.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We liberated the city of Colmar.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They stopped the Bulge fighting with trying to prepare for our big offensive that ended the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In February, we were loaned to the French First Army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- three American divisions went south of the great city of Colmar, and we liberated it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The whole southern Alsace, where-- the Swiss border.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
